Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Pick the @thyme{1} leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks). Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Pop the chunks onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and scatter over the thyme. Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Remove the @confit duck legs{2} from their packaging. Place onto a lined baking tray, skin-side up, and drizzle with a little oil. When the oven is hot, roast the potatoes on the top shelf until golden and the duck on the middle shelf, ~{25-35%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The duck is cooked when piping hot throughout.

Meanwhile, trim and halve the @tri-coloured chantenay carrots{150%g} lengthways (no need to peel). After 5 mins of roasting time, add the carrots to the potato tray and toss together. Cook for the remaining time until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}, turning halfway. While everything roasts, halve, peel and chop the @echalion shallot{1} into small pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a garlic press).

When 15 mins of roasting time remain, heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. When hot, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{60%g} and onion. Stir-fry until golden, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook lardons thoroughly.

Add the @chopped cavolo nero{100%g} and a splash of water and cover until wilted, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> TIP: Remove any tough stalks from the cavolo nero.

Remove the lid, add the garlic, and stir-fry for ~{1%minute} more. Season to taste, then transfer to a #bowl{} and cover to keep warm.

Pour the @water{150%ml}(for the sauce) into the (now empty) pan and bring to the boil on high heat. Stir in the @red wine jus paste{15%g}, then reduce the heat to medium. Allow the sauce to bubble and thicken, stirring regularly, ~{5-6%minutes}. Once glossy and thickened, remove from the heat.

Once everything is ready, transfer the duck to your #plates{} and serve with the thyme roast potatoes, carrots and bacon cavolo nero alongside. Spoon the red wine jus over the duck to finish. Enjoy!